apertium-id-ms
==============
This is a prototype of the Indonesian-Malaysian language pair in Apertium. Currently it only supports translation from Indonesian to Malaysian.

Requirements
============
Install all the following dependencies:

* lttoolbox (http://wiki.apertium.org/wiki/Lttoolbox)
* apertium (http://wiki.apertium.org/wiki/Installation)
* hfst3 (http://wiki.apertium.org/wiki/Hfst)
* foma (http://wiki.apertium.org/wiki/Foma)

Installation
============
Run make to install the linguistic data:

$ make

Testing
============
Test the installation by running the following command:

$ make test

which will translate the story in dev/ directory.

List of files
=============
* apertium-id-ms.id.lexc   - Monolingual dictionary for Indonesian
* apertium-id-ms.id.xfst   - xfst rules for Indonesian
* main-id.foma             - foma script for Indonesian
* id-ms.prob               - Tagger model for Indonesian
* apertium-id-ms.ms.lexc   - Monolingual dictionary for Malaysian
* apertium-id-ms.ms.xfst   - xfst rules for Malaysian
* main-ms.foma             - foma script for Malaysian
* apertium-id-ms.id-ms.t1x - Transfer rules for Indonesian-to-Malaysian translation
* apertium-id-ms.id-ms.dix - Bilingual dictionary

Technical information
=====================
Tag descriptions: http://wiki.apertium.org/wiki/Indonesian_and_Malaysian.